      New Standards for Smart Connected Home

      For the very first time ever, it gives you the power to create your own private network of smart home devices across eco-systems. Now, drop every other smart app when you can simply connect and interact. When you install India’s 1st Panasonic AC enabled with Matter, you are not just installing an AC but you enter a new era of interoperability and you start communicating in the new universal language of smart home connectivity. Making your life better and moving towards a future that actually matters.

      Footnote:

      Source: Euromonitor International Limited, leading brands considered account for over 90% of retail value sales in India in 2022, claim for room ACs only, all retail channels, research as of 01/12/2023”

      Smart Cooling with AI Mode

      AI mode powered by Miraie senses external weather conditions like heat and humidity & automatically manages temperature, mode and fan speed to provide best cooling with optimum power consumption.

      7-in-1 Convertible AC

      While Panasonic Inverter Air Conditioners are truly auto convertible, there is a provision to manually adjust the AC for up to 7 stages of cooling performance ranging from 40% to more than 100%, this can be done via Converti7 button on the remote or on the Miraie app

      A Smarter Way to Control Your Air Conditioner

      Miraie delivers convenient control, connectivity and comfort. Seamlessly adjust temperature, monitor status and change modes right from the Miraie App.With MirAIe, you can switch your Panasonic Air Conditioner on and off from anywhere, anytime. You can even pre-set the AC temperature as per your sleep profiles.

      Custom Sleep Profile

      Indulge in blissful sleep with Panasonic AC's Custom Sleep Profile! Delicately crafted to cultivate an ideal environment for tranquil nights and revitalizing mornings. Experience a personalized haven of supreme comfort with no more midnight chills.

      Intuitive Voice Control

      Introducing intuitive voice control with Google Assistant and Amazon Alexa control compatibility. Using your existing Google assistant or Alexa devices, control your Panasonic air conditioner with just your voice.

      Self Diagnosis

      With the intuitive auto-diagnosis feature, our Air Conditioner is equipped to detect issues in advance and alert users.

      Crystal Clean

      Through defrosting, frosting, cold expansion, and a mechanism to remove all filth that enters the unit, the AC performs self-cleaning with its Crystal Clean feature. The leftover debris that accumulate in the fans and air ducts are often cleaned by the process.

      Stabilizer Free Operation

      Panasonic Air Conditioners are designed to operate under tough conditions with stabilizer free operation for voltage range between 100V-290V. If power fluctuation is beyond the stated limit, then a stabilizer is required.

      Powerful Mode

      As temperatures rise outside, so will indoor temperatures. Being outdoors can keep you uncomfortable and sweaty. But that doesn't mean you have to prolong that discomfort after you set foot indoors. Panasonic air conditioners with POWERFUL mode delivers powerful cooling with strong airflow to cool a room quickly, providing an instant relief during hot days.

      PM 0.1 Filter, Dry Mode

      Equipped with the PM 0.1 Filter to provide dust free, clean air by removing the PM 0.1 particles in the air.

      Equipped with Dry Mode for effective humidity control.

      Energy Saving and Precise Temperature Control

      All-in-One Auto-Convertible Panasonic Air Conditioners adjust the cooling capacity automatically basis the temperature and humidity level inside the room. Enjoy not just hassle-free cooling but save big on energy bills too. The Twin Cool Inverter provides a host of benefits for your comfort, such as quicker cooling upon start-up, constantly maintaining a set temperature, a wider power output range, reduced noise levels and energy savings.

      You can never go wrong with this
      I bought this for my master bedroom which is quite big and ideally a 2 ton model would have been the preferred choice but it was out of my budget and considering the electricity bill of bigger size AC I was determined to get only the 1.5 ton which works for most of the house holds but it was a risk in my case but based on the AC reviews by Vineet Malhotra on YT (VM_ONE Insta handle) I found this AC checking all the boxes for my basic requirements:- should be reliable brand with proven record of after sales services and no hassle of getting spare parts- should be under the budget of 50k including stabilizer and installation charges- should be a 5 star 2023 model- should be a smart AC- should have good cooling (its subjective, what is good for me may not be enough for others) but should not consume much electricity- should have copper wiring- The remote should have backlightPros: Apart from above pointer I took my time and tested the AC performance for more than 2 months and now coming here to share my point of view as this is enough time to test out the AC in various modes or in most of the scenarios to see how well it holds up. I did not wanted it to be one of those 2 week review which does not gives the whole picture.-The deliver with Prime was quick and it was delivered next day and the installation also happened the same day.- The AC is silent and even on full fan speed it does not let you know that it is running. The only time it started making noise when I accidentally pressed some buttons unknowingly and I was not sure what had happened and I had to restart it and change temperature and it returned to normal working. If someone knows what may have went wrong then do let me know.- The AC has auto mode and sleep mode so you can choose the desired mode as per your requirement and it also offers converti7 mode with various combo to chill your room as per your requirement but be mindful the energy consumption will be according to the mode you have selected. More details are provided in the manual. Considering my big room size it never lets me feel that it is still a 1.5 ton AC thanks to its actual capacity of 1.4 ton which lets you push max cooling in this size. Most companies claim 1.5 ton but actual cooling capacity can vary from 1.2 ton to 1.3 ton most of the time. So for this AC it was more in this category compared to any other brand.-The MirAle smart app works without issues and most of the time I just use my iPhone14 to control the functions of AC and it works as advertised.- It is very low power consuming even on daily use basis which is a blessing. After 2 months usage my electricity bill was just little under 5900 and usually per month we were spending 2k-2.5k on an avg. So it only added around 4k max in my electricity bill and probably I will have another bill to play in this current season so for me it seems pretty ok compared to my previous cheap AC from Whirlpool which was giving me headache in terms of electricity bills even when we were not using it that much.- The AC does have an option to turn off the AC panel backlight so it helps while sleeping if someone is used to sleep in pitch dark else. Also the LED is bright enough to keep your room lit to be aware of your surroundings if someone prefers it that way. Many AC's can skip this useful trick to cut costs and it can be a nightmare to not have such an option.- The AC also has auto clean function but I have not tried it so far so will update in case I have any new findings of this feature.Cons: There are not many cons but few things to share with you:- The AC outlet pipe have to be purchased separately which is true however I had to ask the technician to visit again as in the zero day install they did not asked me if I have such accessory or they need to bring it and due to lack of communication (I was in Hospital completing discharge formalities since my son had to go through a surgery and was not in the mindset to think about it sooner when installation guy came to install it) so the customer service team or local dealer/techitian should have advised the same to me as a result I did not operated the AC for a week till this pipe got installed. A cheap accessory that does not let create any mess while AC is running but it should have been addressed quickly or promptly by customer support.- The clear button is also used to turn on/off the AC panel backlight but on the first day of usage it only worked once and then due to some fault in remote it stopped working. For a new AC remote to fail so suddenly only suggests that Panasonic needs to improve the quality of remote. Not that bad but still such a good AC should have an equally matching remote too. The replacement was done promptly though so I was happy with that.- The customer support have indeed improved from Panasonic but it still needs to work on small things and I had to call 2-3 times to get a technician visit with the local service center. Some mistake on my part as the local service guys did not stated that I need to always log complaint on the 1800 toll free number then only complaint will be handled by local service center. Silly of me to think that direct call can be logged but it would have been nice if the technician visiting the site for first time to install have informed me about the same.- The AC remote has lots of mode but I felt the auto mode is not the best may be my room size is big but I found the Cool mode to be working best always. I did not had to use any other fancy modes like converti7 or powerful etc.- The AC remote backlight is not always on it only comes on when you press any button but in dark room you can only the temperature button glowing but if you have to check what mode AC is on and what is the fan speed or swing direction you have to either use your mobile torch or the room LED bulb to actually see the information if you do not like pressing the wrong button. There should be a dedicated button to keep backlight on for more than few seconds. The alternate is to use the smartphone app but not everyone wish to open the smartphone when lying in bed just to look at AC status on remote or if they want to decrease just the fan speed if the air blowing speed is bit uncomfortable.Conclusion: Overall it is a very solid AC in 45k budget (5-6k Stabilizer + 1500 aprox. install charges + 150 bucks for the AC water outlet pipe are additional expenses for me) and I am happy with this purchase. I am planning to buy another one despite small issues with customer service but it was part my shortcoming as well and if someone is considering to purchase a smart AC in this budget then you should definitely give it a try.

      5.0 out of 5 stars Thanda Thanda Cool Cool
      Reviewed in India on 25 April 2024
      Style Name: 1.5 Ton 5 Star | 2024 | NU18ZKY5WVerified Purchase
      The media could not be loaded.
       Two weeks later
      AC is too damn good for its price and category.
      feature packed.

      perks :-
      cooling is phenomenally quick. ( I've a 220 sqft bedroom, ideally 2ton was suitable but trust me 1.5ton substantially delivers a great performance )

      Has Ai feature which gathers all temperature information from indoor & outdoor unit, and selects the cooling temperature accordingly. ( i don't have to manually control AC at all, personally its really fantastic, i leave the AI mode on all the time even at night. )

      MiraI App, love this feature almost makes the remote useless for me, through app you can control the ac entirely, also it will give you consumption data as well, not sure is it totally reliable or not, but wont hurt to have a general idea about usage.

      smart assistant, works seemlesly with amazon alexa.

      Cooling
      i honestly have nothing more to add on its cooling efficiency
      just so coooool , its very quite as well, certainly you wont be bothered by it.
      i leave my ac on all night ( simultaneous use of 6-8 hours should be enough, more than this is not favourable in long run. )

      warranty, Panasonic promises industry standard warranty ( you can register for the warranty on the app itself ).
      am opting to not use stabiliser because this device is capable of handling voltage fluctuations upto 290V~ which is sufficient to handle any sudden fluctuation, considering my city does not has such hight amount of fluctuation scenario.

      Outdoor unit
      i've chosen to fix it right outside my bedroom, which is an ally with good airflow and space, plus OD unit requires shade to perform efficiently.
      so the noise is darn optimal, not too loud or noticeable ( of course am saying from the inside )

      customer support
      initially there was a week long delay, had to call the customer support twice to inform them, ( i totally understand since it was peak of the summer and the technician's were quite packed with work, surely this will vary city to city. please kindly choose to be cordial with CS & technicians )
      they promptly resolved the matter. so yes the after sale support of Panasonic was good and quick.

      design is okeish
      dosen't has different appeal, just same Ac appeal.

      Things to remember

      if this is your first Ac installation then a must read ( if not, skip )
      before installation gather as much information about the process as you could, just a cautionary step ( sometimes technicians are prone to do sh**tty job )
      do not unpack the product on your own, advisable to be done in the presence of technician.
      at the time of installation keep your attention on the process, if they miss any step remind them instantly.
      common step to look out for is vacuuming of the unit, they will try to skip it, it's a safe side thing you get it done anyhow.
      mind you the power cable is not provided due the preferential need of end users requirement, so use a three core 2.5mm wire or as your technician will guide you so. ( use good quality board for the plug, preferably there’s a designated Ac board available from various companies. )
      make sure the indoor unit is fixed slightly tilted towards the drainage pipe outlet. ( avoids the possibility for indoor leak )
      3" inch space is minimum to be left above the ac unit, ( indoor ) for air intake.
      if possible have your indoor & outdoor unit fixed in close proximity, its better for cooling efficiency.
      installation costed Rs 2400 ( Rs 1200+GST, and OD unit stand Rs 999 ) excluding material and electrical work ( this is up to your requirement )
      fixed cost might vary according to state-state.

      rest is 😎 cool.

      hope this helps 👍.

      Bhupender Thakur
      5.0 out of 5 stars You can never go wrong with this
      Reviewed in India on 11 August 2023
      Style Name: 1.5 Ton 5 Star | 2023 | NU18YKY5WVerified Purchase
      I bought this for my master bedroom which is quite big and ideally a 2 ton model would have been the preferred choice but it was out of my budget and considering the electricity bill of bigger size AC I was determined to get only the 1.5 ton which works for most of the house holds but it was a risk in my case but based on the AC reviews by Vineet Malhotra on YT (VM_ONE Insta handle) I found this AC checking all the boxes for my basic requirements:

      - should be reliable brand with proven record of after sales services and no hassle of getting spare parts
      - should be under the budget of 50k including stabilizer and installation charges
      - should be a 5 star 2023 model
      - should be a smart AC
      - should have good cooling (its subjective, what is good for me may not be enough for others) but should not consume much electricity
      - should have copper wiring
      - The remote should have backlight

      Pros: Apart from above pointer I took my time and tested the AC performance for more than 2 months and now coming here to share my point of view as this is enough time to test out the AC in various modes or in most of the scenarios to see how well it holds up. I did not wanted it to be one of those 2 week review which does not gives the whole picture.

      -The deliver with Prime was quick and it was delivered next day and the installation also happened the same day.
      - The AC is silent and even on full fan speed it does not let you know that it is running. The only time it started making noise when I accidentally pressed some buttons unknowingly and I was not sure what had happened and I had to restart it and change temperature and it returned to normal working. If someone knows what may have went wrong then do let me know.
      - The AC has auto mode and sleep mode so you can choose the desired mode as per your requirement and it also offers converti7 mode with various combo to chill your room as per your requirement but be mindful the energy consumption will be according to the mode you have selected. More details are provided in the manual. Considering my big room size it never lets me feel that it is still a 1.5 ton AC thanks to its actual capacity of 1.4 ton which lets you push max cooling in this size. Most companies claim 1.5 ton but actual cooling capacity can vary from 1.2 ton to 1.3 ton most of the time. So for this AC it was more in this category compared to any other brand.
      -The MirAle smart app works without issues and most of the time I just use my iPhone14 to control the functions of AC and it works as advertised.
      - It is very low power consuming even on daily use basis which is a blessing. After 2 months usage my electricity bill was just little under 5900 and usually per month we were spending 2k-2.5k on an avg. So it only added around 4k max in my electricity bill and probably I will have another bill to play in this current season so for me it seems pretty ok compared to my previous cheap AC from Whirlpool which was giving me headache in terms of electricity bills even when we were not using it that much.
      - The AC does have an option to turn off the AC panel backlight so it helps while sleeping if someone is used to sleep in pitch dark else. Also the LED is bright enough to keep your room lit to be aware of your surroundings if someone prefers it that way. Many AC's can skip this useful trick to cut costs and it can be a nightmare to not have such an option.
      - The AC also has auto clean function but I have not tried it so far so will update in case I have any new findings of this feature.

      Cons: There are not many cons but few things to share with you:

      - The AC outlet pipe have to be purchased separately which is true however I had to ask the technician to visit again as in the zero day install they did not asked me if I have such accessory or they need to bring it and due to lack of communication (I was in Hospital completing discharge formalities since my son had to go through a surgery and was not in the mindset to think about it sooner when installation guy came to install it) so the customer service team or local dealer/techitian should have advised the same to me as a result I did not operated the AC for a week till this pipe got installed. A cheap accessory that does not let create any mess while AC is running but it should have been addressed quickly or promptly by customer support.
      - The clear button is also used to turn on/off the AC panel backlight but on the first day of usage it only worked once and then due to some fault in remote it stopped working. For a new AC remote to fail so suddenly only suggests that Panasonic needs to improve the quality of remote. Not that bad but still such a good AC should have an equally matching remote too. The replacement was done promptly though so I was happy with that.
      - The customer support have indeed improved from Panasonic but it still needs to work on small things and I had to call 2-3 times to get a technician visit with the local service center. Some mistake on my part as the local service guys did not stated that I need to always log complaint on the 1800 toll free number then only complaint will be handled by local service center. Silly of me to think that direct call can be logged but it would have been nice if the technician visiting the site for first time to install have informed me about the same.
      - The AC remote has lots of mode but I felt the auto mode is not the best may be my room size is big but I found the Cool mode to be working best always. I did not had to use any other fancy modes like converti7 or powerful etc.
      - The AC remote backlight is not always on it only comes on when you press any button but in dark room you can only the temperature button glowing but if you have to check what mode AC is on and what is the fan speed or swing direction you have to either use your mobile torch or the room LED bulb to actually see the information if you do not like pressing the wrong button. There should be a dedicated button to keep backlight on for more than few seconds. The alternate is to use the smartphone app but not everyone wish to open the smartphone when lying in bed just to look at AC status on remote or if they want to decrease just the fan speed if the air blowing speed is bit uncomfortable.

      Conclusion: Overall it is a very solid AC in 45k budget (5-6k Stabilizer + 1500 aprox. install charges + 150 bucks for the AC water outlet pipe are additional expenses for me) and I am happy with this purchase. I am planning to buy another one despite small issues with customer service but it was part my shortcoming as well and if someone is considering to purchase a smart AC in this budget then you should definitely give it a try.
